white-faced heron
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:Ardea novaehollandiae novaehollandiae ,  occas. also called blue heron and (poss. erron. for white-faced) white-fronted heron, A grey-blue heron with a white face and throat. Self-introduced (?c. date) from Australia, now the commonest heron in NZ.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: also called matuku(-moana)
